# Cursor AI Rules for IB Bot Project

## Documentation & Summaries
- **NO summary documents**: NEVER create summary, results, or completion documents (e.g., SUMMARY.md, CHANGES_SUMMARY.md, FINAL_SUMMARY.md, RESULTS.md, IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md, etc.)
- **NO automatic documentation**: Do not create README files, guide files, or documentation files unless explicitly requested by the user
- Provide brief summaries directly in chat responses only
- Only create documentation files when the user specifically asks for them
- Focus on code and functionality, not documentation

## Code Style
- Follow existing code patterns in the project
- Use clear, descriptive variable names
- Add docstrings for public methods

## Testing
- Run verification after major changes
- Use existing test files in the project
